# FBA Admin Backend

Generated by `fbago init [[ .Module ]] --template admin`.

## Layout

- `cmd/api`: thin HTTP/CLI bootstrap.
- `internal/generated`: deterministic plugin registration; do not edit it.
- `internal/app`: project-owned business modules.
- `plugins.yaml`: enabled official, third-party, and local plugin packages.
- `plugins.lock`: resolved Go module versions and local replacement commits.
- `.env`: local defaults. Real environment variables override this file.

Official Admin features are provided by:

```text
[[ .TemplateModule ]] [[ .TemplateVersion ]]
```

Their implementation source is not copied into this project.

## Commands

```bash
make generate
make check-generated
make test
make build
make run
go run ./cmd/api migrate up
go run ./cmd/api migrate status
```

For a fresh local database, activate the disabled bootstrap administrator:

```bash
go run ./cmd/api admin bootstrap
```

The generated `.env` supplies the local-only password `Admin@Local2026!`, so
the development login is `admin` / `Admin@Local2026!`. The command consumes
that password once; remove or replace `ADMIN_BOOTSTRAP_PASSWORD` before
deployment. To enter a different password through hidden terminal prompts,
remove that setting or override it with an empty value:

```bash
ADMIN_BOOTSTRAP_PASSWORD= go run ./cmd/api admin bootstrap
```

`fbago init` writes a unique 32-byte development JWT secret to `.env`. Rotate
it before deployment or whenever credentials may have been exposed:

```bash
fbago secret generate
fbago secret generate --bytes 64
```

The command prints URL-safe key material only; copy it to `TOKEN_SECRET_KEY` or
`TOTP_ENCRYPTION_KEY` as appropriate.

Add project modules under `internal/app`, list their import paths in
`plugins.yaml`, then run `fbago plugin sync`.

Inspect and apply released plugin module updates separately from generated-file
checks:

```bash
fbago plugin outdated
fbago plugin update --dry-run
fbago plugin update
fbago plugin sync --check
```

To modify the official Admin module through a local checkout or Git submodule:

```bash
fbago module use --path ../fba-go-admin [[ .TemplateModule ]]
fbago plugin sync
```

Remove that override with:

```bash
fbago module reset [[ .TemplateModule ]]
```

Plugin updates reject locally replaced modules. Reset the replacement before
updating to a released version.

When initialization uses `--template-replace`, `go.mod` records that local
checkout. Released initialization defaults to semantic module dependencies.
